content: WEST INDIES WIN CONVINCINGLY! Full-length delivery at the stumps. Liam McCarthy backs away and steers it to deep point for a single. Ireland finish on 194/7, falling short by 62 runs.
Yorker, just past the leg stump. Liam McCarthy backs away for the drive but does not connect.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, just outside off. Liam McCarthy plays at it and gets the outside edge that runs down to the third man region for a streaky boundary.
SIX! THAT'S OUTTA HERE! On a length, on the leg pole. Liam McCarthy makes room and heaves it over the deep square leg fence for a massive hit. Goes all the way into the crowd.
Banged in short, around the right shoulder. Liam McCarthy ducks under it and lets it go.
On a hard length, on the middle and leg. Liam McCarthy makes room and looks to pull but misses.
SIX MORE! THIS IS EVEN BETTER! Full-length delivery, in the slot, around off. Mark Adair makes room and lofts it inside out over deep extra cover boundary for a glorious six.
SIX! ALL THE WAY! Pitched full, around off. Mark Adair clears the front leg and slams it over deep extra cover fence for a cracking hit.
Low full toss, on the middle and leg. Mark Adair looks to flick but it comes off the cue end, rolls back at Holder.
Low full toss on the middle. Clipped toward mid-off for a single.
On a length, just outside off. Liam McCarthy plays and misses.
Fuller than a length, outside off. Mark Adair drags it along the ground to long-on for one.
Low full toss at the stumps. Flicked to deep mid-wicket for one.
On a hard length, on off. Liam McCarthy taps it in front of the point fielder for a single.
Full-length delivery outside off. Mark Adair flays it to deep backward point for a single.
Back of a length delivery on the hip. Liam McCarthy tucks it toward square leg and takes a quick single. A direct hit at the striker's end, but Mark Adair was in.
Back of a length delivery, zips through, around off. Liam McCarthy pulls and misses.
Banged in short, around the right shoulder. Liam McCarthy sways out of the line and lets it pass.
Pitched full, around off. Liam McCarthy makes room and drives it off the cue end to deep extra cover for just a single.
Banged in short, on the leg stump line. Liam McCarthy ducks under it and lets it go.
Full-length delivery on off. Mark Adair lifts it to deep extra cover for a single.
Pitched full, just inside the tramline now. Mark Adair backs away too far, plays, and misses.
WIDE! On a length and just outside the tramline. Left alone. Wide signaled.
Back of a length delivery on the leg pole. Liam McCarthy tucks into the leg side for a run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Romario Shepherd gets among the wickets. Full-length delivery, just outside off. Barry McCarthy gets under it and slices it aerially and straight to Evin Lewis at the deep cover boundary. He makes no mistake and Ireland lose their seventh.
Barry McCarthy c E Lewis b R Shepherd 2 (3b 0x4 0x6)
WIDE! Slower length ball, outside the tramline. Barry McCarthy lets it go. Wide signaled.
SIX! THUMPED! Short of a length delivery, around off. Mark Adair gets on top of the bounce and he has blasted this over the long-on fence for a colossal hit.
Pitched full, and pushed across the batter. Mark Adair swings and misses.
IN THE AIR AND LANDS SAFELY! Slower and shorter, outside off. Barry McCarthy miscues it high toward the deep mid-on region. Falls away from the fielder and they cross for a run.
Yorker, just outside off. Mark Adair squeezes it through backward point for a run.
Floaty slower ball, outside off. Barry McCarthy drives it to deep cover for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Jason Holder gets his second! Short of a good length, outside off. Tim Tector reaches for it and slaps it flat, straight to the throat of Shimron Hetmyer at the deep cover-point boundary who takes a sharp catch. Ireland slide further as Tim Tector departs early.
Tim Tector c S Hetmyer b J Holder 7 (9b 0x4 0x6)
Tosses it on the middle and leg. Tim Tector eases it to long-on for one.
Good length and following Mark Adair outside the leg-stump, as he punches it wide of extra-cover for one.
SIX! BANG! High full toss on the middle and leg. Mark Adair likes it there and launches it over the wide long-on fence for a colossal hit.
WIDE! Too full, outside the tramline. Mark Adair lets it go. Wided.
Tad short, on the middle and leg. Tim Tector pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, on off. Mark Adair chips it to long-off for one.
On a length, outside off. Tim Tector is in the charge and he cuts it to deep point for one.

OUT! SHARP CATCH! Hosein ends with three wickets. Floated full, on the middle. Dockrell makes room and lofts it off the cue end, goes toward the long-on region, where Jason Holder takes a brilliant running catch to his left and above his head. Ireland have lost half of their side now.
George Dockrell c J Holder b A Hosein 15 (8b 3x4 0x6)

Peach of a delivery. Tosses it full and spins late, just outside off. Dockrell swings and misses. Appeal from the keeper for a stumping. The square leg umpire has gone upstairs to check. The replay shows that the foot is grounded inside the crease when the bails come off. NOT OUT it is.
Arm ball, on the middle and leg. George Dockrell works it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR MORE! EASY PICKINGS! Flat, drifted into the pad. George Dockrell transfers the weight back and pulls it hard through backward square leg for another boundary.
FOUR! BANG! Flatter on the middle. George Dockrell makes room and slaps it over the bowler, down the ground for a thumping hit.
Tossed up on a good length on middle. Tim Tector comes down the track and flicks to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! FINDS THE GAP! Full and on the leg. Dockrell backs away and whacks it toward the cow corner region for a cracking boundary to end the over.
Slower through the air, outside off. Tim Tector sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Drifted on the pad. Dockrell works it to short fine leg for one.
On a length, on the middle. George Dockrell turns it to mid-wicket.
FIVE WIDES! Fired in full and down the leg. George Dockrell shimmies down to hack it across the line but misses. Shai Hope fails to collect it and Ireland get five bonus runs.
Floated on off. Eased past the bowler, toward long-off for one.
Tosses it on a length, on the middle and leg. Tim Tector makes room and nudges into the leg side.

OUT! ROSS ADAIR HOLES OUT! Hosein gets two in the over! Bowls it a tad short, around off. Adair hacks it toward the deep mid-wicket region, where Gudakesh Motie takes a sharp catch near the boundary. A handy knock from Ross Adair comes to a close. Ireland are four down.
Ross Adair c G Motie b A Hosein 48 (36b 3x4 4x6)
Flatter arm ball, on the middle. Adair knocks it into the off-side.
Flighted full, on off. Tim Tector taps it toward point and takes a quick single.

OUT! CAUGHT! HOSEIN REMOVES TUCKER! Tosses it on a length, around off. Tucker shimmies down and lofts it high toward the long-on region. Jason Holder there, takes a simple catch. Tucker departs early. Ireland are three down.
Lorcan Tucker (wk) c J Holder b A Hosein 1 (4b 0x4 0x6)
Tosses it full, around off. Tucker shuffles across, looks to slog, but misses.
Flatter arm ball, on off. Tucker knocks it to short extra cover.
Length ball on the leg. Tucker nudges it to backward square leg for one.

OUT! LBW! The golden arm of Roston Chase breaks the partnership! Low full toss on the middle and leg. Harry Tector looks to swipe it across the line but misses and gets pinned in front. Appeal from the bowler and up goes the finger. A decent knock from Tector ends now.
Harry Tector lbw R Chase 38 (25b 4x4 2x6)
Flatter on the leg. Harry Tector plays and misses onto the pad.
Fired in on the middle and leg. Flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker length ball, on the middle and leg. Ross Adair pulls and misses.
The 100-run stand comes up! Tad short, on the middle and leg. Harry Tector pulls it to deep square leg for one.
WIDE! Flatter and angled down the leg. Harry Tector pulls and misses. Wide to start the over.
Hard length and around off, Harry Tector slices it to third man for one. Nelson on the board.
Short of a length and outside off, Harry Tector slashes but misses.
FOUR! Fine shot! Fuller and around off, Harry Tector presents the full face of the bat and drives it firmly through mid off for a boundary.
SIX! Tremendous shot! Alzarri Joseph bangs this into the pitch, on middle. Harry Tector picks up the length early and whacks it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Back of a length and outside off, Ross Adair punches it to sweeper covers for a run.
Right in the blockhole, on middle, Ross Adair digs it back to the bowler.
Floated, full and on off, Ross Adair uses his feet to take it on the full and slaps it to sweeper covers for one more.
Swing and a miss! Flighted, full and around off, Ross Adair goes down for the slog sweep but fails to connect.
Short and on off, Ross Adair punches it to covers.
SIX! SMOKED! Tossed up, full and on middle, in the slot. Ross Adair clears his front leg away and dismisses it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie. New Balls Please!
Flatter, full and on leg, Ross Adair misses his flick as ball goes off his pads toawrds fine leg. Two leg byes.
SIX! Clean hit! Short and around middle. Ross Adair skips down the track and muscles it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
In the blockhole, on leg, Ross Adair tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
A low full toss, on off Ross Adair drills it wide of sweeper covers for a brace.
Romario Shepherd sees the batter back away and serves this full and outside off, Ross Adair fails to reach it.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Tector punches it through covers for one.
Fuller but well outside off, Harry Tector leaves it alone. Wided.
SIX! Outta here! Romario Shepherd bangs this short again, Harry Tector stands tall and hammers it over the deep square leg fence and out of the park for a six.

FOUR! Just wide! Short of a length and on middle, Harry Tector pulls it away aerially wide of deep square leg. Evin Lewis runs to his left and dives but the ball drops in front of him and goes for a boudnary.
Flighted, full and on off, Harry Tector pushes it through covers for one.
Quicker, full and on leg again, Ross Adair fails to get his bat on it and the ball deflects off the pads to short fine. Another leg bye.
Fires one full and on leg, Harry Tector misses his flick and the keeper also fails to stop it. A bye taken.
Flighted, full and on leg, drills it to long on for one.
Slows it up, short and on off, Ross Adair moves back to pull but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Floated, full and on middle, Harry Tector swipes it to short fine.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Fuller and on middle, Ross Adair flicks it away with beautiful timing through mid-wicket for four more runs. Ireland are 60/1 at the end of the Powerplay!

FIVE WIDES! Free runs! Alzarri Joseph errs in line and serves this full and way down the leg side, Ross Adair leaves it alone. Shai Hope behind the stumps decides to save his fingers and does not put in the dive as the ball races to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Slower, hard length and outside off, Ross Adair slashes but misses.
Uppish but safe! Back of a length and on middle, Ross Adair tries to heave it but mistimes it in the air. It lands safely in front of deep mid-wicket. Two taken.
SIX! Connects this time! Short of a length and on middle. Ross Adair gets on top of the bounce this tie, stands tall and dispatches it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Fiery! Alzarri Joseph bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, Ross Adair goes for the pull but misses.
Play and a miss! Good length and on middle, angling in, Ross Adair backs away to steer it away but misses.
FOUR! Nicely done! Hard length but down the leg side, Harry Tector just helps it on its way to the deep backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Ross Adair tries to flick but misses as the ball goes off his pads to short third for a leg bye.
SIX! BANG! Short of a length and well outside off, Ross Adair gets the chance to free his arms and slaps it over deep point for a biggie.
FOUR! Fine shot! Pitched up and on middle, Ross Adair gets fully underneath it and smashes it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Bangs this into the pitch but down the leg, Ross Adair misses his hook. Wided.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller one and outside off, Ross Adair reaches out for it and smacks it over extra covers for a boundary.
Short of a length and on middle, Harry Tector pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length and on leg, follows the batter, Ross Adair backs away to steer it away but misses.
Fuller and on leg, Harry Tector flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Hits the length hard, on middle, Harry Tector goes for the pull but gloves it down. He then kicks it away to prevent the ball roll onto the stumps.
Short of a length and on middle, Harry Tector pulls it away wide of deep square leg. Evin Lewis runs to his left and stops it with his foot. Two runs taken.
Back of a length and on leg, Ross Adair looks to hook it away, but misses and gets hit on the pads as the ball deflects off his thigh pad towards square leg. Leg bye taken.
Fuller and on off, Ross Adair drills it to short covers.
Another short delivery, on off, Harry Tector bunts it to extra covers.
Shortish and around off, Ross Adair pats it wide of mid off for a run.
Quicker, short and on off, Ross Adair stabs it to the off side.
Flatter, short and around off, Ross Adair mistimes his cut to point.
Short and on off, Harry Tector punches it to covers for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Harry Tector tucks it to short fine.

DROPPED! It should have been two in the over for Jason Holder! He pulls his length back slightly, outside off. Ross Adair backs away and looks to go over covers but gets a top edge. The ball flies high in the air behind mid on. Alzarri Joseph backtracks for a while, but he fails to get the balance right and spills the reverse cup. Two taken and Adair gets a life!
Hard length and on leg, Harry Tector fails to glance it away as the ball goes off his pads to fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
FOUR! Good shot! Pitches it up but on the pads, Harry Tector flicks it away with nice timing to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, angling in, Harry Tector misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On a length and on middle, Harry Tector nudges it to mid-wicket.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Jason Holder strikes with his very first delivery! He gets the big fish, Paul Stirling and this is a huge blow for Ireland. Holder begins with a fuller one and around off, shaping away. Stirling throws his bat at it without any footwork. Gets a thick outside edge towards first slip where Rovman Powell takes a sharp catch around his face. Ireland are 13/1!
Paul Stirling (c) c R Powell b J Holder 13 (6b 3x4 0x6)
Short and around off, Ross Adair cuts it to point. 13 runs off the first over!
Flatter, full and on leg, Paul Stirling tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Slows it up, short and on middle, Paul Stirling taps it to covers.

FOUR! Make that three in a row! Tossed up, full and on off again. Paul Stirling stays leg side of the ball and carves beautifully over extra covers for four more runs. The timing was excellent as it almost went for a six.
FOUR MORE! A bit short and on middle and off, Paul Stirling backs away again and punches it sweelty through covers again for another boundary.

FOUR! Paul Stirling and Ireland get underway in style! Akeal Hosein starts with a floater, full and on middle. Stirling moves to the leg side to create room and creams it through covers for a boundary.

SIX! SMOKED! Romario Shepherd ends with a bang! Barry McCarthy goes short again and on middle and gets the treatment. Shepherd stands tall and pulls it with disdain over the deep square leg fence for a biggie. West Indies finishes on a massive 256/5!

A full toss outside off, Romario Shepherd swings wildy but gets an iniside egde onto his pads as the ball drops on the pitch. The batters set off the run and Barry McCarthy runs forward to collect the ball spins away. 250 up for the Windies!
SIX! It is raining sixes in Bready! Barry McCarthy bangs this short and on middle. Romario Shepherd picks up the length early and heaves it over the deep mid-wicket fence for half a dozen more.
Short of a length and on middle, Keacy Carty looks to pull but the ball gets big on him and he miscues the shot. The ball goes up in the air but falls safely beside the pitch. They cross.
FOUR! Streaky! Fuller again and outside off too, Keacy Carty throws his bat at it, slices it a bit but it goes between deep square leg and deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
SIX! Up, up and away! Barry McCarthy goes fuller and just outside off, Keacy Carty extends his arms to get under it and carves it over the deep extra cover fence or a biggie.
SIX! That is a shot and a half! Short of a length and outside off, takes pace off. Romario Shepherd latches on to it, generates the pace and slaps it over the deep point fence for another biggie.
SIX! Gets hold of this one! Pitched up and on middle and leg again, Romario Shepherd this time picks it up and whips it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
A full toss, on middle, angling in, Romario Shepherd tries to slog it away but misses and wears it on the pads.
Bangs in a bouncer but too high, Romario Shepherd leaves it alone. It is given as wide initially, but after getting further information, it is changed to a No Ball. Free hit up next.

OUT! TAKEN! Mark Adair strikes! He goes full and on middle, angling in. Jason Holder clears his front leg to whip it away but does not get the elevation on this one. It goes flat and aerially towards deep mid-wicket, where Ross Adair runs forward and dives in to take a fantastic catch. Holder goes for 18 off 12, and West Indies lose half their side now.
Jason Holder c R Adair b M Adair 18 (13b 2x4 1x6)
Slower, fuller but way down the leg side, Jason Holder lets it go. Wided.
Fuller one and well outside off, Jason Holder shuffles across but leaves it. The umpire does not give it as a wide.
FOUR! Fine shot! A low full toss around off, Jason Holder sets up a solid base and carves it through extra covers for a boundary.

SIX MORE! Liam McCarthy bowls a low full toss, outside off. Keacy Carty throws his bat at it, loses his bottom hand but slices it over the deep point fence for another biggie. A tough outing for the debutant, as this is the most expensive spell by an Irish in T20Is.
Short again and outside off, Keacy Carty backs away and fails to reach it.
SIX! Top shot! Liam McCarthy bangs this into the pitch, on middle. Keacy Carty stays compact in his crease, gets on top and swats it over the bowler's head for a flat six.
FOUR! Good shot! Goes fuller and on middle and off. Keacy Carty backs away to access the off side and and smacks it past mid off for a boundary. 200 up for the Windies!
Short of a length and outisde off, Keacy Carty slashes hard but misses.
Fuller but angling down the leg side, Keacy Carty misses his flick. Wided.
Pitched up and outside off, Jason Holder squeezes it to deep point for a single.
Full again and on middle, shaping in, Jason Holder has no room to work with and tucks it through mid-wicket for one. Good comeback from Adair after getting hit for a six on the first ball.
Goes fuller and outside off, shapes away, Jason Holder gives charge but then lets it go. Not a wide according to the umpire.
Good change of pace, pitched up and on off, Jason Holder bunts it back to the bowler.
Short of a length and on middle, Keacy Carty pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A yorker, angling into leg, Jason Holder misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads to short third. A leg bye is taken.
SIX! Clean strike! Fuller one and around off, in the slot too. Jason Holder gets in line of the ball, extends his arms to reach out and dispatches it over the long off fence for a biggie.
Dragged back, on off, Jason Holder punches it to cover-point for a quick one.
Slows it up, full and on off, Jason Holder dabs it to backward point.
Short again and on leg, Keacy Carty nudges it through mid-wicket for a run.
Short and on middle, Jason Holder pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Gets off the mark nicely! Floated, full and on middle, Jason Holder gets down on one knee and paddles it towards the fine leg fence for a boudnary.

OUT! TAKEN! Ben White gets a wicket now! He serves a googly, full and outside off, turns away. Shimron Hetmyer throws his bat at it but only manages to get an outside edge as the ball loops towards short third where Barry McCarthy takes a dolly. West Indies are 180/4!
Shimron Hetmyer c B McCarthy b B White 15 (7b 3x4 0x6)
Short of a length and on middle, Keacy Carty pulls it wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Swing and a miss! Hits the length hard and around off, shaping away, Keacy Carty swings hard but fails to connect.
Bangs this one into the pitch and well outside off, Keacy Carty leaves it alone thinking it is a wide, but nothing from the umpire.
Back of a length and around off, Keacy Carty cuts it hard but Paul Stirling makes a good stop at point.
EDGED AND FOUR! Short of a length and outside off, Keacy Carty slashes, gets an outside edge that goes wide of short third for a boundary.
Good length and around off, Keacy Carty tries to push it away but misses.
FOUR! Streaky! Hits the length hard and around off, takes off sharply, Shimron Hetmyer tries to play, but the ball flies off rhe shoulder of the bat over short third for four more runs.

FOUR! Good effort but in vain! Bangs this into the pitch, on middle, Shimron Hetmyer heaves it away wide of deep mid-wicket. George Dockrell covers a lot of ground to his left and dives to flick the ball with his backhand inside. The umpires wants to check, and the replay shows that after he flicked the ball, it rolls onto and hits his back and at that time he was touching the ropes. Another boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, Keacy Carty pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Put away! Short and wide outside off, Keacy Carty accepts the width on offer and cuts it powerfully over point for another boundary.
Fuller and around off, Shimron Hetmyer steers it through point fora single.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Short of a length and outside off, Shimron Hetmyer gets the chance to free his arms and crunches it through point for a boundary.
Flighted, full and on middle, Keacy Carty tucks it through mid-wicket and comes back for the second run. Matthew Humphreys finishes an incredible spell with figures of 4-0-16-2.
Shortish and around off, Keacy Carty steers it to short third.
Flatter, short and on off, Shimron Hetmyer punches it to long on for a run.
Short and on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! The Nervous Nineties gets to Evin Lewis! He falls just short of a fine hundred, but he has played an amazing knock of 91 off 44. Matthew Humphreys bowls this quicker, short and on middle. Lewis rocks back to pull, but the ball comes on a bit quicker than he expects. He only manages to slice it in the air towards extra covers, where Paul Stirling takes dolly. Double strike in the over!
Evin Lewis c P Stirling b M Humphreys 91 (44b 7x4 8x6)
Tossed up, full and on middle, Shimron Hetmyer drills it to long on for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! Matthew Humphreys strikes! He deserved the wicket for the way he has bowled here. Humphreys sees the batter step out and darts this one full and well outside off. Rovman Powell is stranded in the middle of the crease and tries to reach out but fails to do so. Lorcan Tucker, behind the stumps sharply moves to his right to collect the ball and break the stumps. A short stay for Powell, and Windies are two down now!
Flatter, full but down the leg side, Rovman Powell misses his flick. Wided.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fires in a yorker, on off, Evin Lewis uses the pace on the ball and squeezes it past short third for a boundary now. 18 runs off the over!

SIX MORE! Easy pickings! Ben White bowls a half-tracker, on middle, begging to be hit. Evin Lewis rocks back quickly and absolutely whacks it over the deep square leg fence for another biggie. It has gone out of the ground. New Balls Please!

SIX! Brute Force! Tossed up, full and on off, Evin Lewis gets right underneath of the ball with the extension of his arms and launches it high and handsomely over the long off fence for a biggie. He moves into the 80s now.
Flighted, full and on off, Rovman Powell goes down across and paddles it to fine leg for a run.
Quicker, short and around off, Rovman Powell misses his cut.

Flatter, full and on middle, Evin Lewis clips it towards deep mid-wicket and sets off for the runs. Liam McCarthy quickly collects and hits the stumps at the bowler's end. Lewis did not expect it but has made his ground.
Short again and on middle, Evin Lewis mistimes his pull this time but the ball lands well in front of deep mid-wicket. Another one.
SIX! BOOM! Back of a length and on middle, sits up nicely for the batter, Evin Lewis pounces on it quickly and hammers it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Loses his line completely and serves this full way, way outside off, almost out of the pitch. Evin Lewis leaves it alone and the umpires check if it is a No Ball or not, but it is just a wide.
An appeal for LBW, but turned down! Fuller and on middle, angling in, Rovman Powell looks to flick but gets an inside edge as the ball goes off his pads towards square leg. They cross.

OUT! TAKEN! Barry McCarthy finally gets the breakthrough for Ireland! Something to cheer about the host as the huge 122-run opening stand has been broken. This is short of a length and on off. Shai Hope stays back and tries to pull it away but goes through the shot a bit early and ends up hitting it much straighter. The ball flies towards long on where Harry Tector takes a fine catch. Fifty and out for the Windies skipper!
Shai Hope (c) c H Tector b B McCarthy 51 (27b 4x4 4x6)
Uppish but safe! Barry McCarthy bangs this one into the pitch, on middle. Evin Lewis looks to pull but gets a top edge that lands just over the backtracking short fine fielder. A single taken.
Fuller and on middle, Evin Lewis bunts it down the pitch.
Low full toss on the middle and leg. Lewis eases it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short and outside off. Hope cuts it to deep point for one.
The top-spinner, on a length, around off. Hope guides it to short third.
Quicker leg break, around off. Hope rocks back for the pull but misses.
SIX! TONKED! Tosses it full, on off. Hope gets low and slams it over the bowler and toward the sight screen for a biggie. Shai Hope brings up his fifty with the hit.
Floated full, on off. Lewis eases it to long-off and takes a single.
FOUR! LUCKY! Short of a good length, just outside off. Hope looks to tuck it across the line but the ball takes the outside edge and flies over the short third fielder for another boundary.
Pitched full, just outside off. Lewis drills it hard but toward the man at deep extra cover for a single.
FOUR! THREE IN A ROW! On a length, angling across the batter. Lewis hammers it through covers for a hat-trick of boundaries.
FOUR MORE! The 100-run partnership comes up now! Low full toss, outside off. Lewis drills it hard through the extra cover region and finds the ropes in a flash.
FOUR! STREAKY! On a length, outside off. Lewis throws his bat and gets the outside edge that flies toward the deep third region for a boundary.
WIDE! Serves it full, outside the tramline. Lewis lets it go. Wide signaled.
SIX! FIFTY FOR EVIN LEWIS! Back of a length, on the middle and leg. Lewis picks the bones out of it and pulls this over deep square leg fence, into the crowd for half a dozen.

DROPPED! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Lewis stands tall and hits it hard and toward the deep cover fielder, Tim Tector, who shells down an easy chance. How costly will it be? The batters cross for a run.
Darted on a length, angling across the batter. Lewis looks to cut but does not connect.
Tosses it on a length, just outside off. Lewis swings across the line but fails to connect.
Flatter on off. Hope rides the bounce and drops it in front of the point fielder for a quick single.
Skiddy length ball, outside off. Hope looks to cut but misses.
Flatter arm ball, on the middle. Hope blocks it into covers.
SIX MORE! BANG! Short again, on the middle and leg. Lewis rocks back and powers it over the deep square leg boundary for back to back sixes.
SIX! PUNISHED! Dropped short, on the middle. Lewis goes back and clubs it powerfully over the cow corner fence for a massive hit.
Too full, on the middle and leg. Lewis gets on one knee and heaves it along the ground to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Shortish leg break, around off. Hope mistimes the pull and it goes on the bounce to the man at long-on for a single.
On a length, spins back into the middle and leg. Lewis eases it to long-on for a single.
Flatter googly, on off. Lewis knocks it to short cover.
Bowls it short and quick on the middle and leg. Lewis goes back and pulls it along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single. West Indies are 70/0 at the end of the powerplay.
Flat and quick at the sticks. Lewis defends from the crease.
Much slower through the air now. Tosses it full, on off. Hope prods and eases it to deep cover for a single.
Darted on a length, outside off. Hope cuts and misses again.
On a length, around off. Hope guides it toward short third and a misfield from Ben White gives away two bonus runs.
Flatter and quicker arm ball, around off. Hope looks to cut but misses.
A dot to end the 21-run over! Bowls it short, into the pitch. Lewis is early into the pull shot and fails to connect.
FOUR MORE! STAND AND DELIVER! Back of a length delivery again, angling across the batter. Lewis gets on top of the bounce and slaps it over the mid-off fielder for back-to-back boundaries.
FOUR! HAMMERED! Back of a length delivery, outside off. Lewis drags it and slams the pull toward the wide of long-on region for a cracking boundary.
Full-length delivery on the leg pole. Hope makes room and squeezes it toward deep mid-wicket for a single.
SIX MORE! PUMPED! Short of a good length, on the middle and leg. Hope picks it early and smokes it over the deep mid-wicket fence for another maximum.
SIX! Liam McCarthy is greeted in style! Slower ball on a length, on the middle and leg. Shai Hope advances and hammers it over the bowler, down the ground for a biggie.
SIX! THAT'S OUTTA HERE! Slower and shorter, around off. Sits up nicely for Lewis, who waits back and slams the pull shot over the deep mid-wicket boundary for a maximum.
Short of a good length, outside off. Lewis mistimes the cut toward the point fielder.
On a length, around off. Lewis guides it to the short third fielder for none.
SIX! BOOM! Slower and shorter, around off. Lewis waits back for it and dispatches this over the deep mid-wicket fence for half a dozen.
Slower bumper, around off. Hope miscues the pull toward square leg region and it takes by the fielder but it will not count since it was a free hit. Single taken.

NO BALL AND FOUR! TOP SHOT! Back of a length delivery, around off. Hope rides the bounce and punches it nicely through the cover region for a lovely boundary. Mark Adair has overstepped. No ball signaled. Free hit coming up.
Pitched full, on the leg pole. Lewis clips it toward backward square leg for a single.
Pitched full, outside the leg stump. Hope makes room to go inside out, but the ball sneaks past him and goes through to the keeper.

FOUR! LUCKY! Good comeback, but the result goes against Barry McCarthy. Bowls it on a length, around off. Hope swings across the line and gets the outside edge that flies to the third man region for a streaky boundary.
SIX! CLEAN STRIKE! On a length, around off. Hope clears the front leg and smashes it with disdain over the long-off fence for half a dozen.
Yorker length delivery, on off. Lewis digs it out and works it toward square leg for a single.
FOUR! BANG! Short of a good length, angling across the batter. Evin Lewis gets on the front foot and slaps it toward the wide long-off region for a thumping boundary.
Full-length delivery, well outside off. Lewis drills it to the extra cover fielder.
Hard length, angled into the middle and leg. Hope drops it into the short leg region.

FOUR! IN THE AIR AND AWAY FOR A BOUNDARY! Short of a good length, around off. Hope makes room and flays it away from the body. It flies off the outer edge toward the deep third region. Liam McCarthy makes a valiant effort near the ropes but fails to prevent the boundary.
Pitched full, at the sticks. Lewis pushes it toward mid-on for a single.
Hard length delivery on the middle. Lewis gets on top of the bounce and looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto the thigh pad.

Short of a good length, on off. Lewis looks to defend from the crease, but it comes off a thigh pad and rolls toward the backward point. Half an appeal from the Irish players, but it was probably going over.
WIDE! Fuller than a length, angling across the tramline. Lewis lets it go. Wide signaled.
Short of a length delivery outside off. Shai Hope gets on top of the bounce and cuts it off the cue end toward deep third for a single.
Very full, on the middle and leg. Shai Hope bunts it toward deep mid-on and takes a single. Tidy start from Matthew Humphreys.
LEG BYE! Flatter, angled into the leg. Evin Lewis turns it round the corner toward short fine leg off his pad as they cross for a leg bye.
Pitched full, around off. Evin Lewis prods forward and defends toward point.
Fuller, angling into off. Shai Hope pushes it to mid-off for a run.
West Indies are away! Tosses it full, outside off. Evin Lewis drives it to cover-point and a half stop from Dockrell allows the single.
Flatter and quicker on off. Evin Lewis defends from the crease.
